            <strong>ðŸ‡·ðŸ‡º Russian gas cutoff:</strong> 
            Russian <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-01-2025-h1-1-gas-supplies" target="_blank">gas supplies</a> to Eastern Europe via Ukraine have halted after a five-year agreement expired. While the European Commission said that the 27-nation bloc was prepared for the scenario, some members, such as Slovakia and Austria, may experience some risk. Robert Fico, the prime minister of Slovakia, threatened to <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-01-2025-h1-2-cut-off-assistance" target="_blank">cut off assistance</a> to Ukrainian refugees as revenge. The country in Europe most heavily impacted is Moldova, a non-EU member, especially <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-01-2025-h1-3-transnistria" target="_blank">Transnistria</a>, where 450,000 residents face heating and hot water shortages.
          </p>
          </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
            <strong>ðŸ‡¦ðŸ‡¿ Azeri-Russian row:</strong> 
            Azerbaijan President Ilham Aliyev alleged that a plane that crashed in Kazakhstan was damaged by electronic jamming and unintentionally <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-01-2025-h2-4-shot-down" target="_blank">shot down</a> by Russian defense systems. He called for Russia to apologize, admit guilt, punish those responsible, and provide compensation. Vladimir Putin expressed condolences but did not acknowledge Russiaâ€™s involvement. Several airlines have since <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-01-2025-h2-5-suspended" target="_blank">suspended</a> flights to Russian cities, potentially straining relations between Russia and Azerbaijan. The two nations had become closer since Azerbaijan's claim over <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-01-2025-h2-6-karabakh" target="_blank">Karabakh</a> and the stationing of Russian peacekeepers in the region after the conflict with Armenia.
          </p>
          </mj-text>

          <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
