          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">On this day in 1948, Burma, now known as Myanmar, officially <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-04-01-2025-ta1-23-gained-independence" target="_blank">gained independence</a> from Britain. After World War II, Burmese leader Aung San took office in the provisional Burmese government formed in 1946. British Prime Minister Clement Attlee and Aung San negotiated the power transfer in 1947. However, the process took a violent turn when the opposition assassinated Aung San in July 1947. That year, Burma left the British Commonwealth, and a new constitution and government were established on January 4, 1948.</p>
          </mj-text>
